This place! WAIT/ATMOSPHERE: The line was long when I went fairly early on a Saturday. But I don't think I waited more than 30+ minutes (which I think is considerably less than I thought on a Saturday morning). The inside is nice - kind of "old bakery-ish" but it is small. There's one large community table and then a few other pretty small tables and a tiny standing bar. SERVICE: Everyone there was friendly but obviously they were working hard to do things quickly. FOOD: Amazing! I only got a couple of traditional items - the ham & cheese croissant and the morning bun - but they were BOTH DELICIOUS. The croissant was perfectly done with a good amount of ham & cheese. It was really filling - which was nice. I also tried the morning bun and it was phenomenal! Delicious.. perfectly gooey and well done with just a hint of citrus taste (which I don't normally like, but worked here since it wasn't overboard). Definitely make it a point to go here! I also tried one of their cakes the night before at a dinner party and it was amazing too. I'm pretty sure nothing is bad here. It's worth the wait in line.

    Overhyped but still good and competent offerings, but only a handful of standout items. Objectively a 3.5 but rounded down for price vs value and wait time. I had Tartine before and after discovering b. which has set my bakery expectations so high it's hard for anything to measure up.

    In descending order of tastiness:
    Banana Cream Tart - best pastry I've had here. Crust is butter, dense and flaky. Parts of the crust are covered with chocolate ganache shell and pockets of caramel. Ripe pieces of banana throughout and swimming in creamy deliciousness. I enjoyed the lack of uniformity in distribution because each bite was a surprise and slightly different because you didn't know how much of what you were going to get (other people might not).
    Chocolate Souffle Cake - deep chocolate flavor and not too sweet. The texture is light, fluffy and smooth to counterbalance the creamy incredibly rich taste.
    Chocolate Eclair - Dense, dense custard filled interior and semisweet dark chocolate frosting. Really enjoyed the rich, eggyness of the custard but found it a little too sweet.
    Frangipane Croissant - A hefty sized croissant, slightly crisp on the outside and a little dry. Caked in almond paste, almond slivers and powdered sugar. I ate half and saved the other half for later.
    Coconut Cream Tart - a perfectly adequate second option if you can't get the banana cream. The coconut is subtle and not overpowering or too gritty in texture.
    Morning Bun - Light layers of slightly fruity, light swirls of pastry dough.
    Lemon Bar - Avoid. So cloyingly sugary, not lemony or tart enough, I couldn't finish it and had to spit it out.
